(f) "Deficiency in service" means a shortcoming or an inadequacy in any service,
which the regulated entity is required to provide statutorily or otherwise, which may
or may not result in financial loss or damage to the customer;

(iii) The Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority of India
established under the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority of
India Act, 1999;

(k) "Non-bank System Participant (NBSP)" means any person other than a bank
participating in a payment system as defined under Section 2 of the Payment and
Settlement Systems Act, 2007 including a 'System Provider'1;

(m) "Regulated Entity (RE)" means a bank or an NBFC or an NBSP or a CIC as
defined in these Directions, or any other entity as may be specified by the Reserve
Bank from time to time;

(a) Banks as defined under clause 3(1)(a) of these Directions and having 10 or
more banking outlets in India, whether such bank is incorporated in India or
outside India;

(b) Implementation of auto-escalation of the partly or wholly rejected complaints to
the Internal Ombudsman within 20 days and adherence with various timelines
indicated in these Directions;

(b) References in the nature of suggestions and commercial decisions of regulated
entity. However, service deficiencies in cases falling under 'commercial decisions'
will be valid complaints for the Internal Ombudsman;
